superMiscConds.notes:
Defendant shall pay supervisory fees to the Department of Corrections;
Defendant shall successfully complete any/all counseling, evaluations, assessments and follow-up as deemed necessary such as mental health evaluation/treatment;
Defendant shall not possess/consume any alcohol, controlled substances (unless prescribed by a physician) or drug paraphernalia;
Defendant shall take all prescriptions as prescribed;
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
Defendant shall report for fingerprinting and photos pursuant to Wis Stats 970.02(7).
Defendant shall not have any contact with victims.
